==Events== *[[404 BC]] &ndash; Admiral [[Lysander]] and King [[Pausanias of Sparta]] blockade Athens and bring the [[Peloponnesian War]] to a successful conclusion. * [[775]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Bagrevand]] puts an end to an [[Armenians|Armenian]] rebellion against the [[Abbasid Caliphate]]. Muslim control over [[Transcaucasia]] is solidified and its Islamization begins, while several major Armenian ''[[nakharar]]'' families lose power and their remnants flee to the [[Byzantine Empire]]. * [[799]] &ndash; After mistreatment and [[disfigurement]] by the citizens of Rome, pope [[Pope Leo III|Leo III]] flees to the [[Francia|Frankish]] court of king [[Charlemagne]] at [[Paderborn]] for protection. *[[1134]] &ndash; The name [[Zagreb]] was mentioned for the first time in the Felician Charter relating to the establishment of the Zagreb Bishopric around 1094. *[[1607]] &ndash; [[Eighty Years' War]]: The Dutch fleet [[Battle of Gibraltar (1607)|destroys]] the anchored Spanish fleet at [[Gibraltar]]. *[[1644]] &ndash; The [[Chongzhen Emperor]], the last Emperor of [[Ming dynasty]] China, commits suicide during a peasant rebellion led by [[Li Zicheng]]. *[[1707]] &ndash; A coalition of Britain, the Netherlands and Portugal is defeated by a Franco-Spanish army at [[Battle of Almansa|Almansa]] (Spain) in the [[War of the Spanish Succession]]. *[[1792]] &ndash; [[Highwayman]] [[Nicolas Jacques Pelletier|Nicolas J. Pelletier]] becomes the first person executed by [[guillotine]]. * 1792 &ndash; "[[La Marseillaise]]" (the French [[national anthem]]) is composed by [[Claude Joseph Rouget de Lisle]]. *[[1804]] &ndash; The western Georgian [[kingdom of Imereti]] accepts the [[suzerainty]] of the [[Russian Empire]]. *[[1829]] &ndash; [[Charles Fremantle]] arrives in HMS ''Challenger'' off the coast of modern-day Western Australia prior to declaring the [[Swan River Colony]] for the United Kingdom. *[[1846]] &ndash; [[Thornton Affair]]: Open conflict begins over the disputed border of [[Texas]], triggering the [[Mexican–American War]]. *[[1849]] &ndash; The [[Governor General of Canada]], [[James Bruce, 8th Earl of Elgin|Lord Elgin]], signs the [[Rebellion Losses Bill]], outraging [[Montreal]]'s [[English Canadian|English]] population and triggering the [[Montreal Riots]]. *[[1859]] &ndash; British and French engineers break ground for the [[Suez Canal]]. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: Forces under [[Union (American Civil War)|U.S.]] [[Admiral]] [[David Farragut]] [[Capture of New Orleans|demand the surrender]] of the [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] city of [[New Orleans|New Orleans, Louisiana]]. *[[1864]] &ndash; American Civil War: The [[Battle of Marks' Mills]]. *[[1882]] &ndash; [[French Third Republic|French]] and [[Nguyễn dynasty|Vietnamese]] troops clashed in [[Tonkin]], when Commandant [[Henri Rivière (naval officer)|Henri Rivière]] [[Battle of Hanoi (1882)|seized]] the [[citadel of Hanoi]] with a small force of marine infantry. *[[1898]] &ndash; [[Spanish–American War]]: The United States declares war on Spain. *[[1901]] &ndash; New York becomes the first U.S. state to require automobile [[license plate]]s. *[[1915]] &ndash; World War I: The [[Battle of Gallipoli]] begins: The invasion of the Turkish Gallipoli Peninsula by British, French, Indian, Newfoundland, Australian and New Zealand troops, begins with landings at [[Landing at Anzac Cove|Anzac Cove]] and [[Landing at Cape Helles|Cape Helles]]. *[[1916]] &ndash; [[Anzac Day]] is commemorated for the first time on the first anniversary of the landing at ANZAC Cove. *[[1920]] &ndash; At the [[San Remo conference]], the principal [[Allies of World War I|Allied Powers of World War I]] adopt a resolution to determine the allocation of Class "A" [[League of Nations mandate]]s for administration of the former [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]]-ruled lands of the Middle East. *[[1938]] &ndash; [[U.S. Supreme Court]] delivers its opinion in ''[[Erie Railroad Co. v. Tompkins]]'' and overturns a century of federal common law. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Merkið]], the flag of the [[Faroe Islands]] is approved by the [[British occupation of the Faroe Islands|British occupation government]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; The [[United Negro College Fund]] is incorporated. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[Elbe Day]]: [[United States Armed Forces|United States]] and [[Soviet Armed Forces|Soviet]] troops meet in [[Torgau]] along the River [[Elbe]], cutting the ''[[Wehrmacht]]'' of [[Nazi Germany]] in two. * 1945 &ndash; [[Liberation Day (Italy)]]: The [[Nazi Germany|Nazi]] occupation army surrenders and leaves Northern Italy after a general partisan insurrection by the [[Italian resistance movement]]; the puppet [[Italian Social Republic|fascist regime]] dissolves and [[Benito Mussolini]] is captured after trying to escape. This day was set as a [[Public holidays in Italy|public holiday]] to celebrate the Liberation of Italy. * 1945 &ndash; [[United Nations Conference on International Organization]]: Founding negotiations for the [[United Nations]] begin in [[San Francisco]]. * 1945 &ndash; The last German troops retreat from Finland's soil in Lapland, ending the [[Lapland War]]. Military acts of Second World War end in Finland. *[[1951]] &ndash; [[Korean War]]: Assaulting Chinese forces are forced to withdraw after heavy fighting with UN forces, primarily made up of Australian and Canadian troops, at the [[Battle of Kapyong]]. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Francis Crick]] and [[James Watson]] publish "[[Molecular Structure of Nucleic Acids: A Structure for Deoxyribose Nucleic Acid]]" describing the [[double helix]] structure of [[DNA]]. *[[1954]] &ndash; The first practical [[Solar cell#History of solar cells|solar cell]] is publicly demonstrated by [[Bell Labs|Bell Telephone Laboratories]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; The [[Saint Lawrence Seaway]], linking the North American [[Great Lakes]] and the Atlantic Ocean, officially opens to shipping. *[[1960]] &ndash; The United States Navy submarine {{USS|Triton|SSRN-586|6}} completes the [[Operation Sandblast|first submerged circumnavigation of the globe]]. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Robert Noyce]] is granted a [[patent]] for an [[integrated circuit]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Nguyen Hue Offensive]]: The [[North Vietnam]]ese 320th Division forces 5,000 [[South Vietnam]]ese troops to retreat and traps about 2,500 others northwest of [[Kontum]]. *[[1974]] &ndash; [[Carnation Revolution]]: A leftist military [[coup]] in Portugal overthrows the authoritarian-conservative ''[[Estado Novo (Portugal)|Estado Novo]]'' regime and establishes a democratic government. *[[1975]] &ndash; As [[People's Army of Vietnam|North Vietnamese forces]] close in on the [[South Vietnam]]ese capital [[Saigon]], the Australian Embassy is closed and evacuated, almost ten years to the day since the first Australian troop commitment to South Vietnam. *[[1981]] &ndash; More than 100 workers are exposed to radiation during repairs of at the [[Tsuruga Nuclear Power Plant]] in Japan. *[[1982]] &ndash; [[Israel]] completes its withdrawal from the [[Sinai Peninsula]] per the [[Camp David Accords]]. *[[1983]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: American schoolgirl [[Samantha Smith]] is invited to visit the [[Soviet Union]] by its leader [[Yuri Andropov]] after he read her letter in which she expressed fears about [[nuclear warfare|nuclear war]]. * 1983 &ndash; ''[[Pioneer 10]]'' travels beyond [[Pluto]]'s orbit. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Mswati III]] is crowned King of [[Swaziland]], succeeding his father [[Sobhuza II]]. *[[1988]] &ndash; In [[Israel]], [[John Demjanjuk]] is sentenced to death for [[war crime]]s committed in World War II. *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Violeta Chamorro]] takes office as the [[President of Nicaragua]], the first woman to hold the position. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Michele Alboreto]] is killed while testing an [[Audi R8 (race car)|Audi R8]] at the [[EuroSpeedway Lausitz|Lausitzring]] in Germany. *[[2004]] &ndash; The [[March for Women's Lives]] brings between 500,000 and 800,000 protesters,<!-- per AP and BBC --> mostly pro-choice, to Washington D.C. to protest the [[Partial-Birth Abortion Ban Act]] of 2003, and other restrictions on [[abortion]]. *[[2005]] &ndash; The final piece of the [[Obelisk of Axum]] is returned to [[Ethiopia]] after being stolen by the invading Italian army in [[1937]]. * 2005 &ndash; [[Bulgaria]] and [[Romania]] sign accession treaties to join the [[European Union]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; [[Boris Yeltsin]]'s funeral: The first to be sanctioned by the [[Russian Orthodox Church]] for a head of state since the funeral of Emperor [[Alexander III of Russia|Alexander III]] in 1894. *[[2015]] &ndash; Nearly 9,100 are killed after [[April 2015 Nepal earthquake|a massive 7.8 magnitude earthquake strikes Nepal]].
